# NOTE: the published tarball is driven entirely by package.json "files"
# (allowlist: dist, themes, scripts, and "!dist/**/*.map" to drop source maps).
# npm does NOT consult this root .npmignore while "files" is present, so it is
# INERT for `npm publish` today. It is kept as an intent marker / safety net for
# the case where the "files" allowlist is ever removed, and for other tooling
# that reads .npmignore. If you drop "files", these rules take effect.

# Source maps — not needed by consumers
*.map
dist/**/*.map

# TypeScript build metadata
*.tsbuildinfo

# Source & tooling (never in the allowlist anyway)
src/
tsconfig.json
Jakefile
.github/
.editorconfig
.prettierrc
.nvmrc
